==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Apperception
<hw>Ap`per*cep"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>ad-</ets> + <ets>perception</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>apperception</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>The mind's
perception of itself as the subject or actor in its own states;
perception that reflects upon itself; sometimes, intensified or
energetic perception.</def> <rj><au>Leibnitz. Reid.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This feeling has been called by philosophers the
<qex>apperception</qex> or consciousness of our own existence.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Apperil</ent>⟦br⟧
